cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a novel layer for deep convolutional neural networks to model pairwise feature interactions in image recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the parameterization and computational cost of the proposed layer, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper validates the effectiveness of the proposed layer on several datasets, indicating a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) as well.
